article.headline: Wagner 75, Chicago St 68 (OT)
article.story: PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Courtney Pritchard scored six of his 18 points in overtime and Wagner overcame Royce Parran's tying 3-pointer at the end of regulation play to beat Chicago State 75-68 Monday. Pritchard's 3-pointer got Wagner (2-6) started in overtime and he also hit three free throws in the final 1:24. Parran scored 22 points to help Chicago State open an 11-point lead in the second half, but Wagner rallied and took the lead at 58-55 on Pritchard's two free throws with six seconds remaining. Parran's 3-pointer with three seconds left tied it. Teoine Carroll scored 22 points as Wagner got its second straight victory in the Pittsburgh Holiday Hoops Tournament, a six-team exempt event in which each team played four times. Chicago State (1-10) lost its fourth straight game in the tournament despite Parran's 22 points, Tony Weeden's 16 and Jeleel Akindele's 15. Chicago State has lost its last 29 games against Division I opponents.
